## 12. Performance Analysis

### 12.1 Encryption Performance

**Bottleneck: File I/O and RSA encryption**

```
Operation              Time (per 1MB file)
──────────────────────────────────────────
Read file:            1-5 ms
Generate AES keys:    <1 ms
RSA encrypt key:      10-50 ms
AES encrypt data:     1-5 ms
Write output:         1-5 ms
──────────────────────────────────────────
Total:                ~13-66 ms per MB

Throughput: 15-75 MB/second
```

### 12.2 Decryption Performance

**Bottleneck: RSA decryption (single operation)**

```
Operation              Time (per 1MB file)
──────────────────────────────────────────
Read header:          <1 ms
RSA decrypt key:      10-50 ms
AES decrypt data:     1-5 ms (chunked)
Write output:         1-5 ms
──────────────────────────────────────────
Total:                ~12-61 ms per MB

Throughput: 16-80 MB/second
```

### 12.3 Scalability

**Concurrent Requests (Multithreaded):**
- Web server can handle multiple simultaneous requests
- Each thread: ~50-100 concurrent connections
- Actual limit: Number of system file handles, CPU cores

**Memory Usage:**
```
Per Encryption (100 MB file):
  File buffer:        100 MB
  RSA context:        <1 MB
  AES context:        <1 MB
  JSON overhead:      ~2 MB
  ─────────────────────────
  Total:              ~103 MB

Per Decryption (100 MB file):
  Input buffer:       4 KB (chunk)
  Output buffer:      4 KB (chunk)
  RSA context:        <1 MB
  AES context:        <1 MB
  ─────────────────────────
  Total:              ~2 MB (constant, memory efficient)
```

