## Appendix A: Key Code Snippets

### A.1 Encryption Overview
```cpp
// User-facing API
bool encryptFile(const std::string& inputPath, const std::string& outputPath) {
    if (!rsaPublicKey) return false;
    return encryptFileHybrid(inputPath, outputPath, rsaPublicKey);
}

// Core implementation
bool encryptFileHybrid(...) {
    // 1. Read file into memory
    // 2. Generate random AES key & IV
    // 3. Encrypt AES key with RSA
    // 4. Encrypt file with AES
    // 5. Write output file with format: [encrypted_key_len] + [encrypted_key] + [IV] + [encrypted_data]
}
```

### A.2 Decryption Overview
```cpp
// User-facing API
bool decryptFile(const std::string& inputPath, const std::string& outputPath) {
    if (!rsaPrivateKey) return false;
    return decryptFileHybrid(inputPath, outputPath, rsaPrivateKey);
}

// Core implementation
bool decryptFileHybrid(...) {
    // 1. Read encrypted_key_len
    // 2. Read encrypted_key
    // 3. Read IV
    // 4. Decrypt AES key with RSA
    // 5. Decrypt file data with AES (chunked for memory efficiency)
}
```

### A.3 Base64 Encoding
```cpp
std::string base64Encode(const unsigned char* buf, size_t len) {
    // Convert binary data to Base64 string
    // Uses standard alphabet: A-Z, a-z, 0-9, +, /
    // Adds padding with = characters
    // Returns Base64 encoded string
}
```

